The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Sunday, April 18, 2004 				 Woman burnt to death
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Inability to bear a child cost a 32-year-old woman her life. Sushmita Das was allegedly burnt to death by her in-laws on Saturday morning in Belghoria, on the citys northern fringes.																								Police said Sushmitas father-in-law, mother-in-law and brother-in-law were arrested on charges of murder. Her husband Atanu is absconding. Sushmita was found in the kitchen with severe burn injuries. She was pronounced dead at the hospital.																								Sushmitas brother Niloy Sarkar alleged that her in-laws started torturing her when they came to know that she could not conceive. We often heard her in-laws abusing her, said a neighbour.
